.TH BUNPY-PM-LOCK 1 "2026-04-27" "bunpy" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bunpy-pm-lock \- regenerate bunpy.lock from pyproject.toml
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bunpy pm lock
.RB [ \-\-check ]
.RB [ \-\-index
.IR url ]
.RB [ \-\-cache-dir
.IR path ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Walks
.B [project].dependencies
in
.IR ./pyproject.toml ,
runs the same naive picker
.BR bunpy-add (1)
uses, and writes
.I ./bunpy.lock
with one
.B [[package]]
row per direct dependency. No install. The lockfile freezes the
resolved version, wheel filename, URL, and sha256 from the PyPI
index so a re-run on a second machine resolves to the same artefact.
.PP
The header carries a
.B content-hash
derived from the sorted, trimmed dep specs joined by newlines.
A cheap byte compare detects pyproject drift without re-resolving.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-check
Verify the lockfile against
.I ./pyproject.toml
and exit non-zero on drift: the lockfile is missing, the
content-hash differs, or the lockfile holds an entry that
.B [project].dependencies
no longer lists. No PyPI traffic, no rewrite.
.TP
.BI \-\-index " url"
Override the PEP 691 simple index. Defaults to
.IR https://pypi.org/simple/ .
.TP
.BI \-\-cache-dir " path"
Override the cache root. Defaults to
.I $BUNPY_CACHE_DIR
or the platform XDG default.
.SH SCOPE
v0.1.4 lands the writer plus reader. There is no transitive walk
yet; the lockfile records only the direct dependencies that
.BR bunpy-add (1)
and
.B pm lock
resolve today. The PubGrub resolver in v0.1.5 fills transitive
entries against the same schema, version 1.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ./pyproject.toml
Source of
.B [project].dependencies
and the content-hash inputs.
.TP
.I ./bunpy.lock
Output of
.BR pm lock .
Sorted by PEP 503 normalised name. LF line endings. Byte-stable.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Zero on a successful write. Non-zero on a missing pyproject, an
unresolvable spec, or (with
.BR \-\-check )
any drift.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bunpy-pm (1),
.BR bunpy-add (1),
.BR bunpy (1).
